          "arguments": {
            "content": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/webidl/Request.webidl\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/fetch/Request.h\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/fetch/Request.cpp\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/webidl/Response.webidl\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/fetch/Response.h\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/fetch/Response.cpp\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/webidl/Headers.webidl\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/fetch/Headers.h\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/fetch/Headers.cpp\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/webidl/FetchEvent.webidl\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/serviceworkers/ServiceWorkerEvents.h\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/serviceworkers/ServiceWorkerEvents.cpp\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"Cross-Org WebIDL to DOM Binding Discovery for Fetch API\\n\\nThe Fetch API in Mozilla Firefox consists of four main DOM interfaces defined in WebIDL and implemented in C++:\\n\\n1. Request (dom/webidl/Request.webidl)\\n   - Defines the DOM interface for HTTP requests with properties like method, url, headers, mode, credentials, cache, redirect, integrity, and keepalive\\n   - C++ Binding Header: dom/fetch/Request.h\\n   - C++ Implementation: dom/fetch/Request.cpp\\n   - The Request class extends FetchBody and implements the WebIDL interface via Request_Binding\\n\\n2. Response (dom/webidl/Response.webidl)\\n   - Defines the DOM interface for HTTP responses with properties like status, statusText, ok, type, url, and redirected\\n   - C++ Binding Header: dom/fetch/Response.h\\n   - C++ Implementation: dom/fetch/Response.cpp\\n   - The Response class extends FetchBody and wraps InternalResponse, implementing the WebIDL interface via Response_Binding\\n\\n3. Headers (dom/webidl/Headers.webidl)\\n   - Defines the DOM interface for HTTP headers with methods like append, delete, get, set, and has\\n   - C++ Binding Header: dom/fetch/Headers.h\\n   - C++ Implementation: dom/fetch/Headers.cpp\\n   - The Headers class is backed by InternalHeaders and provides the public-facing Headers object\\n\\n4. FetchEvent (dom/webidl/FetchEvent.webidl)\\n   - Defines the DOM interface for fetch events in service workers, extending ExtendableEvent\\n   - Contains properties like request, preloadResponse, clientId, resultingClientId, and handled\\n   - C++ Binding Header: dom/serviceworkers/ServiceWorkerEvents.h\\n   - C++ Implementation: dom/serviceworkers/ServiceWorkerEvents.cpp\\n   - The FetchEvent class is defined at line 132 of ServiceWorkerEvents.h and extends ExtendableEvent\\n\\nAll WebIDL interfaces are exposed to Window and Worker contexts (or specifically to ServiceWorker for FetchEvent). The C++ implementations handle the actual binding code generation and provide the interface between JavaScript and the internal Gecko implementation.\"\n}\n",
